William Smith, 14, wanted to remind himself of his mother, Alison Overton .
He wore her favourite bandana around the house and sprayed her perfume .
But months later, while her grandmother was looking after him, he decided to play a prank on her .
On the day of his death, he stayed home while his grandmother took his younger brothers out, asking her to bring him back chicken nuggets as a lunchtime treat .
Inquest heard the teenager had 'settled back in well' at school following his mother's death .